  "text": "Folate transport across epithelia and into systemic tissues occurs via the reduced folate carrier, the folate reception family, and the recently discovered proton-coupled folate transporter. [CITATION_1] Nutritional deficiencies, particularly those involving B-group vitamins and folate, important cofactors of homocysteine (Hcy) metabolism, are commonly related with high circulating levels of Hcy.",
